A square piece of glass and a triangular piece of glass are joined to make a window. The area of the triangular piece of glass is $40$ square feet. Find the total area of the window.

\begin{tikzpicture}
% Square
\draw (0,0) -- (2,0) -- (2,2) -- (0,2) -- cycle;
% Triangle on top
\draw (0,2) -- (1,3) -- (2,2);
% Labels
\node[above left] at (0,2) {8 ft};
\node[below] at (1,0) {10 ft};
\end{tikzpicture}

The total area of the window is \underline{\hspace{1cm}} square feet.
